      "role": "PythonProgramming_Expert",
      "content": "We need to fetch the C++ source code from the URL: `https://rosettacode.org/wiki/Sorting_algorithms/Quicksort`\n\nNext steps:\n1. Fetch the C++ code from the given URL.\n2. Compile and run the C++ code with the array [35, 12, 8, 99, 21, 5].\n3. Return the sum of the third and fifth integers in the sorted list.\n\nLet's proceed to fetch the C++ code first. Here\u2019s a Python script to do that.\n\n```python\nimport requests\nfrom bs4 import BeautifulSoup\n\nurl = \"https://rosettacode.org/wiki/Sorting_algorithms/Quicksort\"\nresponse = requests.get(url)\nsoup = BeautifulSoup(response.text, 'html.parser')\n\n# Locate the C++ code segment\ncode_section = soup.find('pre', class_='cpp')\ncpp_code = code_section.get_text()\n\n# Save the C++ code to a file\nwith open('quicksort.cpp', 'w') as file:\n    file.write(cpp_code)\n\nprint(\"C++ code fetched and saved to quicksort.cpp\")\n```\n\nLet\u2019s execute this script to fetch and save the C++ code to a file."
